Section 15: Task Scheduling in Spring
    Lecture 79: Scheduled Tasks in Spring

1. Setup Spring scheduling
 1.1 Add @EnableScheduling annotation into the CommonBeanConfig.java
    - ej.springframework.config.CommonBeanConfig.java

2. Implements LoginService Interface
  - es.springframework.services.security.LoginService.java (interface)
  2.1 Implements resetFailedLogins() method

3. Create new LoginServiceImpl.java to implements LoginService interface
  - es.springframework.services.security.LoginServiceImpl.java
  - This class implements LoginService interface
 3.1 Add spring service stereotype
    - Add @Service annotation above the LoginServiceImpl class
 3.2 Inject dependency to use the UserService
    - Declare UserService property
    - Implement setter method for UserService property
    - Add @Autowired annotation to Injecting dependency that above setter method
 3.3 Override and implements LoginService interface's method
    - Add @Scheduled(..) annotation to use the spring schedule

4. Refactoring LoginFailureEventHandler.java

5. Test
 5.1 Start SpringmvcApplication Server
 5.2 Look at the Server console to check scheduled task
 5.3 Open web browser: http://localhost:8080
 5.4 Try Login with wrong user id and password ( To test try to about 3 times )
